Enforce security compliance
Manage infrastructure, identity, and access across consumer organizations <br>Manage <a data-href="vSAN" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsan/vsan.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">vSAN</a> storage
<br>Manage networking in <a data-href="NSX" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/nsx/nsx.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">NSX</a> <br>Link <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="vCenter Server" data-href="vCenter Server" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/core-components/vcenter-server.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">vCenter</a> instances for centralized inventory management
<br>Manage certificates across the <a data-href="VCF Fleet" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/fleet-and-domain-model/vcf-fleet.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Fleet</a>
<br>Manage passwords across the <a data-href="VCF Fleet" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/fleet-and-domain-model/vcf-fleet.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Fleet</a>
<br>Manage tags across the <a data-href="VCF Fleet" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/fleet-and-domain-model/vcf-fleet.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Fleet</a>
<br>Manage the configuration settings of <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="vCenter Server" data-href="vCenter Server" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/core-components/vcenter-server.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">vCenter</a> instances and <a data-href="vSphere Cluster" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/object-model/inventory-objects/vsphere-cluster.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">vSphere Cluster</a>s. <br>Prepare the collection of VM-base workload <a data-href="Blueprint" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/blueprint.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Blueprint</a>s and infrastructure services for the organization and end users <br>Provision <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Virtual Machine" data-href="Virtual Machine" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/object-model/virtual-machine-primitives/virtual-machine.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VM</a>s
Provision Kubernetes clusters
<br>Provision <a data-href="vSphere Pod" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/platform-extensions/vsphere-supervisor/architecture-and-core-concepts/vsphere-pod.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">vSphere Pod</a>s
Provision persistent volumes
Provision secret stores
Install container registries
<br>After this summary, <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="vSphere" data-href="vSphere" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/vsphere.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">checking out vSphere</a>—one of the core abstraction layers of VCF—could provide further clarity.]]></description><link>./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/about-vcf.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/About VCF.md</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Volkan Özçelik]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 28 Dec 2025 17:34:36 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[VCF SDKs, APIs, and CLIs]]></title><description><![CDATA[<a href="./https://vcf.wtf?query=tag:lifecycle" class="tag is-unresolved" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow" data-href="#lifecycle">#lifecycle</a><br>See also: <a data-href="Gated SDK" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/vcf-enablers/gated-sdk.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Gated SDK</a><br>In VMware Cloud Foundation, “VCF SDK APIs and CLIs” are programmable control surfaces that expose VCF capabilities for automation, integration, and at-scale operations. They sit above the infrastructure components (<a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="vCenter Server" data-href="vCenter Server" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/core-components/vcenter-server.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">vCenter</a>, <a data-href="NSX" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/nsx/nsx.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">NSX</a>, <a data-href="vSAN" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsan/vsan.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">vSAN</a>) and below higher-level portals, giving you deterministic, supportable ways to drive the platform.┌──────────────────────────────────────────────┐
