Approved storage classes
<br>Approved <a data-href="NSX Segment" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/nsx/object-model/nsx-segment.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">NSX Segment</a>s
<br>Approved <a data-href="HA" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/object-model/cluster-services/ha.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">HA</a> / backup models
Users pick “what”, not “how”.DSM automates:
Database-aware backups
Snapshots
Restore workflows
Optional replication patterns
This is database lifecycle, not just VM lifecycle.DSM targets enterprises modernizing gradually, not cloud-native purists.This distinction is important.
SDDC Manager: <br>Patches <a data-href="ESX" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/core-components/esx.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">ESX</a>, <a data-href="NSX" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/nsx/nsx.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">NSX</a>, <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="vCenter Server" data-href="vCenter Server" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/core-components/vcenter-server.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">vCenter</a> DSM: Patches databases
