STIG (Security Technical Implementation Guide) is a <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="https://disa.com/" rel="noopener nofollow" class="external-link is-unresolved" href="https://disa.com/" target="_self">DISA</a> / <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Department_of_Defense" rel="noopener nofollow" class="external-link is-unresolved" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_Department_of_Defense" target="_self">U.S. DoD</a>–defined security hardening standard.
STIG is:
=======
<br>Check out <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Governance" data-href="Governance" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/governance-and-compliance/governance.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">what governance means in the context of VCF</a>.]]></description><link>./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/governance-and-compliance/vcf-roles-and-permissions.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Concepts/Governance and Compliance/VCF Roles and Permissions.md</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Volkan Özçelik]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 25 Dec 2025 22:22:08 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Governance]]></title><description><![CDATA[<a href="./https://vcf.wtf?query=tag:tenancy" class="tag is-unresolved" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow" data-href="#tenancy">#tenancy</a>Governance in VCF is the set of mechanisms that decide who is allowed to request which platform capabilities, under what constraints, with what approvals, and for how long — before anything is created.<br><a data-href="VCF Automation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/vcf-automation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Automation</a> governs entitlement and lifecycle decisions, including lease expiry and grace periods, but vSphere Supervisor remains the execution authority and only acts when Automation explicitly requests a change.
VCF-A governance is front-door, human-aware, policy-driven
It’s about entitlement, approval, and lifecycle
It is not a security monitoring system
It is not a Terraform-style reconciler
It is exactly what service providers and large enterprises need to avoid chaos
What Governance is NOT:Governance does not watch workloads.
It decides whether they are allowed to exist in the first place.Governance (VCF Automation)
├── Organizations
├── Projects
├── Blueprints
├── Entitlements
├── Approvals
├── Quotas
└── Leases Execution (vSphere / Supervisor)
├── Namespaces
├── Resource pools
├── Networks
└── Workloads
Nothing in the execution layer knowns governance exists.
Governance defines who may open the door.
Execution decides what happens after they are inside the house.
In other words, governance is “pre-creation” control, not runtime policing.<br>From here, <a data-href="Policy" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/governance-and-compliance/policy.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Policy</a>, <a data-href="Policy as Code" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/governance-and-compliance/policy-as-code.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Policy as Code</a>, and <a data-href="STIG" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/governance-and-compliance/stig.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">STIG</a> are all good candidates to check out.]]></description><link>./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/governance-and-compliance/governance.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Concepts/Governance and Compliance/Governance.md</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Volkan Özçelik]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Thu, 25 Dec 2025 22:19:49 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Management Domain]]></title><description><![CDATA[![[workload-domain-b8d5ddd7-899b-4c34-8947-4acbd57f8f72.webp]The Management Domain is created during the deployment or convergence process by the&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Installer" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/vcf-enablers/vcf-installer/vcf-installer.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Installer</a>. It contains the <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="VCF Management Components" data-href="VCF Management Components" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/architectural-constructs/vcf-topology/vcf-management-components.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">management components</a> of the&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Instance" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/fleet-and-domain-model/vcf-instance.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Instance</a> and, for the first VCF Instance,&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Operations" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-operations/vcf-operations.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Operations</a> and&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Automation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/vcf-automation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Automation</a>.In addition to the components that are common for each&nbsp;VCF Domain, the management domain includes the&nbsp;
<br><a data-href="SDDC Manager" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/sddc-manager/sddc-manager.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">SDDC Manager</a> <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Virtual Appliance" data-href="Virtual Appliance" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/virtual-appliance/virtual-appliance.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Appliance</a> and the&nbsp;<a data-href="Fleet Management" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-operations/platform-operations-and-services/platform-services-and-management/managing-the-cloud/fleet-management.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Fleet Management</a> <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Virtual Appliance" data-href="Virtual Appliance" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/virtual-appliance/virtual-appliance.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Appliance</a>, that adds workflows for infrastructure management automation to the&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Operations" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-operations/vcf-operations.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Operations</a> instance for the&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Fleet" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/fleet-and-domain-model/vcf-fleet.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Fleet</a>.
