tion</a> governs entitlement and lifecycle decisions, including lease expiry and grace periods, but <a data-href="vSphere Supervisor" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/platform-extensions/vsphere-supervisor/vsphere-supervisor.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">vSphere Supervisor</a> remains the execution authority and only acts when <a data-href="VCF Automation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/vcf-automation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Automation</a> explicitly requests a change.
<br><a data-href="VCF Automation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/vcf-automation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Automation</a> governance is front-door, human-aware, policy-driven
It’s about entitlement, approval, and lifecycle
It is not a security monitoring system
It is not a Terraform-style reconciler
It is exactly what service providers and large enterprises need to avoid chaos
What Governance is NOT:Governance does not watch workloads.
It decides whether they are allowed to exist in the first place.Governance (VCF Automation)
├── Organizations
├── Projects
├── Blueprints
├── Entitlements
├── Approvals
├── Quotas
└── Leases Execution (vSphere / Supervisor)
├── Namespaces
├── Resource pools
├── Networks
└── Workloads
Nothing in the execution layer knowns governance exists.
Governance defines who may open the door.
Execution decides what happens after they are inside the house.
In other words, governance is “pre-creation” control, not runtime policing.<br>From here, <a data-href="Policy" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/governance-and-compliance/policy.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Policy</a>, <a data-href="Policy as Code" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/governance-and-compliance/policy-as-code.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Policy as Code</a>, and <a data-href="STIG" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/governance-and-compliance/stig.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">STIG</a> are all good candidates to check out.]]></description><link>./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/governance-and-compliance/governance.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Concepts/Governance and Compliance/Governance.md</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Volkan Özçelik]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 28 Dec 2025 15:20:04 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[VCF Advanced Services]]></title><description><![CDATA[<a href="./https://vcf.wtf?query=tag:architecture" class="tag is-unresolved" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow" data-href="#architecture">#architecture</a>VCF Advanced Services provide additional add-on functionality to the platform.The following sections summarize some of the VCF Advanced Services.<br>VMware Live Recovery is used to build powerful cyber and data resiliency for&nbsp;<a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="VMware Cloud Foundation" data-href="VMware Cloud Foundation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/vmware-cloud-foundation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF</a>.It provides ransomware and disaster recovery in a unified management experience, accelerated recovery, and simplified consumption.You can use Data Services Manager to build enterprise-hardened data services with high availability, performance, backup, and monitoring.<br>You can use VMware Private AI Foundation to run NVIDIA NIM microservices on&nbsp;<a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="VMware Cloud Foundation" data-href="VMware Cloud Foundation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/vmware-cloud-foundation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF</a>, which support AI models from NVIDIA and others in the community, and NVIDIA AI tools and frameworks.<br>You can use vDefend for built-in zone and application microsegmentation, threat detection and response, lateral security, ransomware and APT protection, reduced attack surface, and zero trust enforcement across&nbsp;<a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="VMware Cloud Foundation" data-href="VMware Cloud Foundation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/vmware-cloud-foundation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF</a> environments.<br>VMware Avi Load Balancer is a software-defined platform deeply integrated with&nbsp;<a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="VMware Cloud Foundation" data-href="VMware Cloud Foundation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/vmware-cloud-foundation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF</a> private cloud, delivering local and global load balancing, Kubernetes ingress, web application and API security and application analytics.<br>Network Observability extends the&nbsp;<a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="VMware Cloud Foundation" data-href="VMware Cloud Foundation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/vmware-cloud-foundation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF</a> management capabilities with end-to-end visibility into the network overlay, underlay, and applications hosted in a public or hybrid cloud.The solution provides actionable insights to automatically pinpoint problems, resulting in lower internal resource costs and faster issue resolution, quickly getting end-users back to revenue-producing activities.<br>How about checking out consumption abstractions such as <a data-href="Organization" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/organization.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization</a>, <a data-href="Project" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/project.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Project</a>, and <a data-href="Blueprint" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/blueprint.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Blueprint</a>.]]></description><link>./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/vcf-capabilities/vcf-advanced-services.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Concepts/Design and Abstractions/VCF Capabilities/VCF Advanced Services.md</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Volkan Özçelik]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 28 Dec 2025 15:18:46 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[VCF Instance]]></title><description><![CDATA[<a href="./https://vcf.wtf?query=tag:architecture" class="tag is-unresolved" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow" data-href="#architecture">#architecture</a><br>VCF Instance is the compute, storage, networking virtual infrastructure that runs business workloads. A&nbsp;VCF Instance consists of&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Domain" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/architectural-constructs/vcf-topology/vcf-domain/vcf-domain.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Domain</a>s: a <a data-href="Management Domain" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/architectural-constructs/vcf-topology/vcf-domain/management-domain.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Management Domain</a> and <a data-href="Workload Domain" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/architectural-constructs/vcf-topology/vcf-domain/workload-domain.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Workload Domain</a