<br>The corporate identity provider is the centralized source of digital identities for the enterprise, which provides authentication and identity assertion. You connect the corporate identity provider to <a data-href="VCF Fleet" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/fleet-and-domain-model/vcf-fleet.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Fleet</a> components by using <a data-href="VCF Identity Broker" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/vcf-identity-broker/vcf-identity-broker.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Identity Broker</a>.<br><a data-href="VCF Identity Broker" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/vcf-identity-broker/vcf-identity-broker.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Identity Broker</a> enables a VCF Single Sign-On implementation and streamlines authentication across different&nbsp;<br>
<a data-href="VCF Fleet" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/fleet-and-domain-model/vcf-fleet.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Fleet</a> components.The table below summarizes several single sign-on models that VMware Cloud Foundation uses:<br>Check out <a data-href="VCF Operations Orchestrator" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-operations/platform-operations-and-services/platform-services-and-management/workflow-management/vcf-operations-orchestrator.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Operations Orchestrator</a> to see how VCF automates workflow-based tasks at various layers of the stack.]]></description><link>./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-operations/platform-operations-and-services/identity-and-access/vcf-single-sign-on.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Control Planes/VCF Operations/Platform Operations and Services/Identity and Access/VCF Single Sign-On.md</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Volkan Özçelik]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 28 Dec 2025 05:47:11 GMT</pubDate><enclosure url="./https://vcf.wtf/assets/vidb-a9030c92-6fbe-4251-a1ed-61494feee0f6.original.svg" length="0" type="image/svg+xml"/><content:encoded>&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;./https://vcf.wtf/assets/vidb-a9030c92-6fbe-4251-a1ed-61494feee0f6.original.svg&quot;&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Security Management]]></title><description><![CDATA[<a href="./https://vcf.wtf?query=tag:security" class="tag is-unresolved" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow" data-href="#security">#security</a> <a href="./https://vcf.wtf?query=tag:operations" class="tag is-unresolved" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow" data-href="#operations">#operations</a> <br>The Security Management area of <a data-href="VCF Operations" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-operations/vcf-operations.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Operations</a> includes capabilities such as Security Operations, Event Auditing, and Compliance Checks.
