Manage Catalog Approval Requests
<br><a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="User Roles" data-href="User Roles" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/organization-management/user-roles/user-roles.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">← Back to User Roles</a>]]></description><link>./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/organization-management/user-roles/project-administrator.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Control Planes/VCF Automation/Tenancy and Access Control/Organization Management/User Roles/Project Administrator.md</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Volkan Özçelik]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 28 Dec 2025 05:43:57 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Organization Administrator]]></title><description><![CDATA[<a href="./https://vcf.wtf?query=tag:tenancy" class="tag is-unresolved" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow" data-href="#tenancy">#tenancy</a> <a href="./https://vcf.wtf?query=tag:governance" class="tag is-unresolved" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow" data-href="#governance">#governance</a> <br>An Organization Administrator can access the <a data-href="Organization" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/organization.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization</a> portal and add users and groups to the <a data-href="Organization" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/organization.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization</a>.Organization Administrators can:
<br>Manage <a data-href="Project" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/project.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Project</a>s and <a data-href="Project User" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/organization-management/user-roles/project-user.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Project User</a>s
Configure integrations, such as Git
<br>Manage <a data-href="Blueprint" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/blueprint.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Blueprint</a>s and Catalog Items
<br>Manage <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Supervisor Namespace" data-href="Supervisor Namespace" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/platform-extensions/vsphere-supervisor/supervisor-internals-and-platform-integration/control-and-consumption/supervisor-namespace.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">namespaces</a> and associated resources
<br>Fully access <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Supervisor Namespace" data-href="Supervisor Namespace" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/platform-extensions/vsphere-supervisor/supervisor-internals-and-platform-integration/control-and-consumption/supervisor-namespace.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">namespaces</a> that they did not create
<br>Manage new <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="VCF Private Cloud" data-href="VCF Private Cloud" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/architectural-constructs/vcf-topology/vcf-private-cloud.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VPC</a>s and associated resources
<br>See all <a data-href="Project" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/project.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Project</a>s and all Deployments
Create and manage Content Libraries
<br>Create and manage <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Policy" data-href="Policy" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/governance-and-compliance/policy.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">policies</a> on resources and deployments
Create and manage event subscriptions
<br><a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="User Roles" data-href="User Roles" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/organization-management/user-roles/user-roles.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">← Back to User Roles</a>]]></description><link>./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/organization-management/user-roles/organization-administrator.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Control Planes/VCF Automation/Tenancy and Access Control/Organization Management/User Roles/Organization Administrator.md</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Volkan Özçelik]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 28 Dec 2025 05:43:49 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Organization Management]]></title><description><![CDATA[<a href="./https://vcf.wtf?query=tag:tenancy" class="tag is-unresolved" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow" data-href="#tenancy">#tenancy</a> <a href="./https://vcf.wtf?query=tag:governance" class="tag is-unresolved" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow" data-href="#governance">#governance</a> <br><a data-href="VCF Automation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/vcf-automation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Automation</a> improves <a data-href="Governance" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/governance-and-compliance/governance.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Governance</a> for users and resources by enabling <a data-href="Organization Administrator" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/organization-management/user-roles/organization-administrator.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization Administrator</a>s create and assign projects and vSphere Namespaces tailored for different application teams.<br><a data-href="Organization Administrator" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/organization-management/user-roles/organization-administrator.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization Administrator</a>s can set resource limits and policies while delegating network management through Virtual Private Clouds (<a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="VCF Private Cloud" data-href="VCF Private Cloud" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/architectural-constructs/vcf-topology/vcf-private-cloud.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VPC</a>s) for application teams.<br>Additionally, <a data-href="Policy as Code" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/governance-and-compliance/policy-as-code.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Policy as Code</a> enables organization administrators to enforce instance-centric policies for Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS) resources from a central location for compliance and reducing the risk of human error.<br>In, <a data-href="VCF Automation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/vcf-automation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Automation</a>, an <a data-href="Organization" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/organization.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization</a> is a top level entity that represents a line of business or a tenant. Each organization operates in a secure and isolated environment where users can access only allocated services and resources.<br><a data-href="Organization" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/organization.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization</a>s consume resources and cloud services from a <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Resource Pool" data-href="Resource Pool" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/object-model/inventory-objects/resource-pool.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">shared pool of resources</a>. The resources allocated to organizations can be further allocated to application teams which are modeled in&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Automation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/vcf-automation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Automation</a> as <a data-href="Project" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/project.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Project</a>s.<br><a data-href="Organization" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/organization.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization</a>s have users with varying levels of permissions depending on their role and duties.<br><a data-href="Organization" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/organization.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization</a>s in&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Automation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/vcf-automation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Automation</a> are created by the Provider Administrator in the&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Automation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/vcf-automation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Automation</a> Provider Management Portal.<br>Each <a data-href="Organization" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/organization.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization</a> has its own Organization Portal where users log in to consume resources and services. Every organization has its own identity source that they connect to and can import users from.<br>Organizations enable line-of-business or tenant [Organization Administrator]]s to further organize and <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Governance" data-href="Governance" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/governance-and-compliance/governance.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">govern</a> resources that are allocated to them among application teams through the following capabilities:
<br>Resource management for <a data-href="Project" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/project.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Project</a> teams.
<br>Centralized content management for the <a data-href="Organization" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/organization.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization</a>.
Policy-based governance on usage of resources.
Quota-based management of networking resources.
<br><a data-href="Workflow" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-operations/platform-operations-and-services/platform-services-and-management/workflow-management/workflow.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Workflow</a> orchestration and extensibility through event subscriptions.
<br><a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="vCF Identity Broker" data-href="vCF Identity Broker" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/vcf-identity-broker/vcf-identity-broker.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Integration with identity providers</a> of their choice.
<br><a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="VCF Automation" data-href="VCF Automation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/vcf-automation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">← Back to “VCF Automation”</a>]]></description><link>./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/organization-management/organization-management.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Control Planes/VCF Automation/Tenancy and Access Control/Organization Management/Organization Management.md</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Volkan Özçelik]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 28 Dec 2025 05:43:25 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Project Management]]></title><description><![CDATA[<a href="./https://vcf.wtf?query=tag:tenancy" class="tag is-unresolved" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow" data-href="#tenancy">#tenancy</a> <a href="./https://vcf.wtf?query=tag:governance" class="tag is-unresolved" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow" data-href="#governance">#governance</a> <br><a data-href="Project" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/project.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Project</a>s in&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Automation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/vcf-automation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Automation</a> <a data-href="Organization" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/organization.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization</a>s provide a logical grouping of users and the infrastructure that they are assigned.<br><a data-href="Project" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/project.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Project</a>s are used to represent real world teams which are in charge of development or operations. Each <a data-href="Project" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/project.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Project</a> has one or more <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Supervisor Namespace" data-href="Supervisor Namespace" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/platform-extensions/vsphere-supervisor/supervisor-internals-and-platform-integration/control-and-consumption/supervisor-namespace.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">namespaces</a> assigned to it. Each <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Supervisor Namespace" data-href="Supervisor Namespace" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/platform-extensions/vsphere-supervisor/supervisor-internals-and-platform-integration/control-and-consumption/supervisor-namespace.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">namespace</a> is an envelope of resources where applications can be deployed. Access controls for <a data-href="Project" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/project.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Project</a>s are governed by pre-defined roles.<br>&nbsp;<a data-href="Organization Administrator" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/organization-management/user-roles/organization-administrator.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization Administrator</a>s can create and attach one or more <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Supervisor Namespace" data-href="Supervisor Namespace" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/platform-extensions/vsphere-supervisor/supervisor-internals-and-platform-integration/control-and-consumption/supervisor-namespace.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">namespaces</a> to a project. Administrators can also delete a namespace at any time, which dissociates the <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Supervisor Namespace" data-href="Supervisor Namespace" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/platform-extensions/vsphere-supervisor/supervisor-internals-and-platform-integration/control-and-consumption/supervisor-namespace.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">namespace</a> from the project.&nbsp;<br>
Every <a data-href="Organization" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/organization.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization</a> comes with a default project. The default project doesn’t have users or namespaces. The <a data-href="Organization Administrator" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/organization-management/user-roles/organization-administrator.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization Administrator</a> can change the name, description of the default project, and add users and namespaces to the default project.<br>&nbsp;A namespace class is a template that is used to create <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Supervisor Namespace" data-href="Supervisor Namespace" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/platform-extensions/vsphere-supervisor/supervisor-internals-and-platform-integration/control-and-consumption/supervisor-namespace.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">namespaces</a>. All components of a namespace, including limits on CPU, memory, and storage utilization, VM classes and storage classes, and content libraries can be defined as a reusable template. Namespace classes are created and maintained by <a data-href="Organization Administrator" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/organization-management/user-roles/organization-administrator.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization Administrator</a>s.<br>&nbsp;Infrastructure quota assigned to an organization can be subdivided and assigned to project teams in the form of <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Supervisor Namespace" data-href="Supervisor Namespace" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/platform-extensions/vsphere-supervisor/supervisor-internals-and-platform-integration/control-and-consumption/supervisor-namespace.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">namespaces</a>]. Namespaces are isolated resource pools in which resources like VMs, <a data-href="VKS" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/platform-extensions/vsphere-supervisor/supervisor-internals-and-platform-integration/kubernetes-runtimes/vks/vks.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VKS</a> clusters, and volumes can be provisioned. <a data-href="Organization Administrator" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/organization-management/user-roles/organization-administrator.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization Administrator</a>s can override the resource limits specified in a namespace class during namespace creation.<br>&nbsp;The resource limits of a namespace can be satisfied from capacity in one or more <a data-href="vSphere" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/vsphere.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">vSphere</a> zones. When creating a namespace, <a data-href="Organization Administrator" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/organization-management/user-roles/organization-administrator.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization Administrator</a>s can select which zones the namespace can use.&nbsp;Namespaces count towards the organization quota. The sum total of resource limits of all created namespaces cannot exceed the organization quota.How many projects and namespaces you create depends on your organization needs.
<br><a data-href="Project" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/project.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Project</a>s: Multiple projects are used when isolation boundaries between project teams are required. Only project members can access deployments and resources available to a project. Fewer projects are desired when isolation requirements can be traded off for a simpler operating model.
<br><a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Supervisor Namespace" data-href="Supervisor Namespace" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/platform-extensions/vsphere-supervisor/supervisor-internals-and-platform-integration/control-and-consumption/supervisor-namespace.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Namespace</a>s: Multiple namespaces are used when strict resource limits are needed for each application. Namespaces are logical constructs that can be used to define application boundaries. Each application can be deployed on a namespace with prescribed resource limits for CPU, memory, and storage. For instance, a group of VMs and <a data-href="VKS" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/core-runtimes/vsphere/platform-extensions/vsphere-supervisor/supervisor-internals-and-platform-integration/kubernetes-runtimes/vks/vks.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VKS</a> clusters that make up an application can be logically grouped together in a namespace.
<br><a data-href="User Roles" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/organization-management/user-roles/user-roles.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">User Roles</a> is the next logical place to explore after here. Or you can check out <a data-href="Organization Management" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/organization-management/organization-management.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization Management</a>.]]></description><link>./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/tenancy-and-access-control/organization-management/project-management.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Control Planes/VCF Automation/Tenancy and Access Control/Organization Management/Project Management.md</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Volkan Özçelik]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 28 Dec 2025 05:43:18 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Provider Management]]></title><description><![CDATA[<a href="./https://vcf.wtf?query=tag:tenancy" class="tag is-unresolved" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow" data-href="#tenancy">#tenancy</a> <a href="./https://vcf.wtf?query=tag:governance" class="tag is-unresolved" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow" data-href="#governance">#governance</a> <br>IT teams and Cloud Service Providers can model <a data-href="Multi-Tenancy" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/tenancy-in-vcf/multi-tenancy.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Multi-Tenancy</a> by using the concept of <a data-href="Organization" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/consumption-abstractions/organization.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Organization</a>s in&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Automation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/vcf-automation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Automation</a>.This approach allocates resources and manages users specific to each Organization.This capability provides isolated environments with dedicated network setup. IT Teams and CSPs can monitor resource usage, control permissions, and provide managed services while ensuring security through comprehensive network isolation.<br><a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="VCF Automation" data-href="VCF Automation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/vcf-automation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">← Back to “VCF Automation”</a>]]></description><link>./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/provider-management/provider-management.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Control Planes/VCF Automation/Provider Management/Provider Management.md</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Volkan Özçelik]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 28 Dec 2025 05:43:08 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Management Domain]]></title><description><![CDATA[<a href="./https://vcf.wtf?query=tag:architecture" class="tag is-unresolved" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow" data-href="#architecture">#architecture</a> <a href="./https://vcf.wtf?query=tag:lifecycle" class="tag is-unresolved" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow" data-href="#lifecycle">#lifecycle</a><br><img alt="workload-domain-b8d5ddd7-899b-4c34-8947-4acbd57f8f72.webp" src="./https://vcf.wtf/assets/workload-domain-b8d5ddd7-899b-4c34-8947-4acbd57f8f72.webp" target="_self"><br>The Management Domain is created during the deployment or convergence process by the&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Installer" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/vcf-enablers/vcf-installer/vcf-installer.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Installer</a>. It contains the <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="VCF Management Components" data-href="VCF Management Components" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/architectural-constructs/vcf-topology/vcf-management-components.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">management components</a> of the&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Instance" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/fleet-and-domain-model/vcf-instance.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Instance</a> and, for the first VCF Instance,&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Operations" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-operations/vcf-operations.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Operations</a> and&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Automation" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-automation/vcf-automation.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Automation</a>.In addition to the components that are common for each&nbsp;VCF Domain, the management domain includes the&nbsp;
<br><a data-href="SDDC Manager" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/sddc-manager/sddc-manager.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">SDDC Manager</a> <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Virtual Appliance" data-href="Virtual Appliance" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/virtual-appliance/virtual-appliance.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Appliance</a> and the&nbsp;<a data-href="Fleet Management" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-operations/platform-operations-and-services/platform-services-and-management/managing-the-cloud/fleet-management.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Fleet Management</a> <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Virtual Appliance" data-href="Virtual Appliance" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/virtual-appliance/virtual-appliance.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Appliance</a>, that adds workflows for infrastructure management automation to the&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Operations" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/control-planes/vcf-operations/vcf-operations.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Operations</a> instance for the&nbsp;<a data-href="VCF Fleet" href="./https://vcf.wtf/vcf/concepts/design-and-abstractions/fleet-and-domain-model/vcf-fleet.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Fleet</a>.
