<br>Organization administrators can set resource limits and policies while delegating network management through Virtual Private Clouds (<a data-href="VPC" href=".html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VPC</a>s) for application teams. <br>Additionally, <a data-href="Policy as Code" href=".html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Policy as Code</a> enables organization administrators to enforce instance-centric policies for Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS) resources from a central location for compliance and reducing the risk of human error.]]></description><link>vcf/main-componets/engine/vcf-a/organization-management.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Main Componets/engine/VCF-A/Organization Management.md</guid><pubDate>Sat, 20 Dec 2025 17:02:42 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Cloud Services]]></title><description><![CDATA[VCF Automation (<a data-href="VCF-A" href=".html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF-A</a>) provides a set of cloud services which are accessible on a self-service basis using multiple interfaces, including UI, CLI, and API.<br>With this interface, users can provision the following types of <a data-href="workload" href=".html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">workload</a>s:
VMs
Kubernetes workloads
Networking
Volumes
Secret stores
Databases
Harbor container registries
External DNS
Certificates
AI workloads
<br>Additionally, application teams can also provision resources on a self-service basis from Catalogs which are backed by pre-configured <a data-href="workload template" href=".html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">workload template</a>s. These self-service options help developers focus on application development instead of managing the underlying infrastructure.]]></description><link>vcf/main-componets/engine/vcf-a/cloud-services.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Main Componets/engine/VCF-A/Cloud Services.md</guid><pubDate>Sat, 20 Dec 2025 16:52:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Security Management]]></title><description><![CDATA[The security management area of VCF Operations includes capabilities such as Security Operations, Event Auditing, and Compliance Checks.
Security Operations: The Security Operations dashboard is designed to provide a comprehensive view of your security posture in VCF.
Events Auditing: Event auditing provides visibility into platform interaction changes across the VCF infrastructure and insights into suspicious access events and policy violations. Compliance: Ensure compliance for your VCF infrastructure and cloud environments against optimum configurations, maintaining a consistent configuration across SDDC components, reducing organizational and business risk.
]]></description><link>vcf/main-componets/engine/vcf-o/security-management.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Main Componets/engine/VCF-O/Security Management.md</guid><pubDate>Sat, 20 Dec 2025 04:28:09 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Workload Mobility]]></title><description><![CDATA[<a data-href="VCF Operations" href="vcf/main-componets/engine/vcf-o/vcf-operations.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">VCF Operations</a> <a data-href="HCX" href=".html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">HCX</a> is a workload mobility platform for migration and interconnection of workloads within and across VCF <a data-href="private cloud" href=".html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">private cloud</a>s.You can perform secure and automated migrations without requiring changes to applications or network configurations. Important features include multiple migration types, such as live and bulk migration, as well as network extension, which preserves existing IP addresses and network topologies. Thus, you can place workloads based on business requirements. The platform minimizes downtime during migrations, improves scalability, and supports compliance and security throughout workload transitions.]]></description><link>vcf/main-componets/engine/vcf-o/workload-mobility.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Main Componets/engine/VCF-O/Workload Mobility.md</guid><pubDate>Sat, 20 Dec 2025 04:25:55 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Workload Placement]]></title><description><![CDATA[Is the <a data-href="vMotion" href=".html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">vMotion</a>, or is there something more?]]></description><link>vcf/main-componets/engine/vcf-o/workload-placement.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Main Componets/engine/VCF-O/Workload Placement.md</guid><pubDate>Sat, 20 Dec 2025 03:15:41 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[FinOps and Capacity]]></title><description><![CDATA[Cost management helps you analyze your infrastructure expenses. In this way, you can identify areas that are most suitable to use capacity management for optimal utilization of your resources.You can use the FinOps or <a data-href="cost management" href="vcf/main-componets/engine/vcf-o/cost-management.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">cost management</a> capabilities to monitor infrastructure-related costs and associated services or license expenses with greater precision.Capacity Management consists of 3 sets of capabilities: assess, optimize and plan.Capacity optimization helps you right-size or reclaim any underutilized or wasted resources.
<br><a data-href="Workload Placement" href="vcf/main-componets/engine/vcf-o/workload-placement.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">Workload Placement</a> lets you optimize virtual machines and storage across clusters to reduce resource contention and maintain optimum system performance.
By using What-If Analysis, you can plan for an increase or decrease in workload or capacity requirements in your virtual infrastructure.
]]></description><link>vcf/main-componets/engine/vcf-o/finops-and-capacity.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Main Componets/engine/VCF-O/FinOps and Capacity.md</guid><pubDate>Sat, 20 Dec 2025 03:15:28 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[cost management]]></title><description><![CDATA[is <a data-href="FinOps and Capacity" href="vcf/main-componets/engine/vcf-o/finops-and-capacity.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener nofollow">FinOps and Capacity</a>]]></description><link>vcf/main-componets/engine/vcf-o/cost-management.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Main Componets/engine/VCF-O/cost management.md</guid><pubDate>Sat, 20 Dec 2025 03:13:19 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Performance Monitoring]]></title><description><![CDATA[Performance monitoring ensures applications have continuous access to resources and AI-driven troubleshooting and remediation enables faster time to resolution of issues while keeping costs down. Manage, monitor and troubleshoot your applications by collecting application metrics from your virtual machines.
A VCF Operations management pack, is a software package that allows you to monitor, manage, and troubleshoot infrastructure by collecting metrics, events, and alerts from the integrated system.]]></description><link>vcf/main-componets/engine/vcf-o/performance-monitoring.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Main Componets/engine/VCF-O/Performance Monitoring.md</guid><pubDate>Sat, 20 Dec 2025 03:12:06 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Workload Operations]]></title><description><![CDATA[Workload operations ensure that critical applications are running properly by monitoring its performance, availability and end-user experience. For container-based applications, VCF Operations provides native integration with vSphere Supervisor which enables automatic monitoring of Supervisor instances and vSphere Kubernetes Service (VKS) clusters at a granular level, shortening troubleshooting time.]]></description><link>vcf/main-componets/engine/vcf-o/workload-operations.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">VCF/Main Componets/engine/VCF-O/Workload Operations.md</guid><pubDate>Sat, 20 Dec 2025 02:18:00 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Operations Management]]></title><description><![CDATA[VCF Operations provides capabilities designed to monitor, diagnose, and manage the health and security of your VCF environments, providing real-time insights and long-term strategic guidance.
